statement.title: Content
statement.content: One day, Jiameier is tidying up the room,and find some coins. Then she throws the coin to play.Suddenly,she thinks of a problem ,that if throw n times coin ,how many situations of no-continuous up of the coin. Hey,Let's solve the problem.

statement.title: Standard Input
statement.content:
The first of input is an integer $T$ which stands for the 
number of test cases. For each test case, there is one integer
$n$ ($1\leq n\leq 1000000000$) in a line, indicate the times of throwing coins.

statement.title: Standard Output
statement.content: The number of all situations of no-continuous up of the coin, moduled by $10000$.

statement.title: Samples
statement.content:
Input Output
3 1 2 32 3 5
